  "summary": "nolimit-x ships heavily obfuscated payload tree with child_process + HTTP POST exfiltration shape",
  "details": "The package contains a hidden directory (.ad/) holding 40+ heavily obfuscated JavaScript files using hex-mangled identifier obfuscation (_0xNNNNNN naming). One of these files,.ad/x0.js, combines require('child_process') with HTTP POST and host-identifier reads (hostname) — the canonical command-execution + exfiltration primitive. Sibling files include sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, phone-validator.js, and web-command.js, suggesting an SMS/SMTP abuse + command execution toolkit hidden under an.ad/ dotdir. Combined signals: (1) systematic identifier obfuscation across an entire 40+ file payload tree (no legitimate package obfuscates its source this aggressively), (2) child_process spawn paired with HTTP POST and host identifiers in a single file, (3) payload concealed in a leading-dot directory designed to avoid casual inspection. The package name and structure provide no legitimate explanation for this composition. Installing or loading this package exposes the host to remote command execution and host-data exfiltration.",
